diff --git a/SOLUTION.md b/SOLUTION.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..fd5da8a
--- /dev/null
+++ b/SOLUTION.md
@@ -0,0 +1,8 @@
+The cache did not refresh an entry's recency after a successful `get`, so a
+recently read entry could still be evicted as though it were the least recently
+used. Successful reads now move their key to the most-recently-used end.
+
+`put` also evicted an entry whenever the cache was full, even when it was merely
+updating an existing key. Eviction is now performed only when a new key must be
+inserted into a full cache; updates retain the other entries and refresh the
+updated key's value, timestamp, and recency.
